## Fields

- `years_experience_min` — number of years, one decimal allowed, or `null` if not stated. Convert months to years (`6 months` → `0.5`, `18 months` → `1.5`).
- `years_experience_max` — number of years, one decimal allowed, or `null`.
- `education_level` — one of: `"none_required"`, `"secondary_school"`, `"vocational"`, `"bachelor"`, `"master"`, `"phd"`, `"professional_degree"`, or `null` if not stated.
- `education_strict` — `true` if the education level is strictly required; `false` if preferred but not required; `null` if no education is mentioned.
- `degree_fields` — English tags, e.g. `["computer_science", "electrical_engineering"]`, `["nursing"]`, `["business_administration"]`. Empty array if none.
- `required_skills` — array of objects:
  ```
  {"skill": "<English-normalized name>", "years_min": <int|null>, "category": "<one of the categories below>"}
  ```
- `required_languages` — ISO-639-1 codes for spoken languages required (e.g. `["en", "de"]`). **Do not put spoken languages in `required_skills`.**
- `required_certifications` — English-normalized certification names.
- `security_clearance` — one of: `"none"`, `"us"`, `"uk"`, `"nato"`, `"eu"`, `"other"`, or `null` if not mentioned. Use `"none"` only when the posting explicitly says no clearance is required.
- `physical_requirements` — array of strings, e.g. `["lift up to 50 lbs", "stand for 8 hours"]`. Verbatim or lightly paraphrased.
- `background_check_required` — `true` / `false` / `null`. Use `false` only when the posting explicitly says no background check is required; use `null` when not mentioned.
- `driving_license_required` — one of: `"none"`, `"standard"`, `"commercial"`, `"hazmat"`, `"other"`, or `null`. Use `"none"` only when the posting explicitly says no license is required.

